data.content:
Yes! MSTest supports `ValueTuple` with `DynamicData`, which gives you strong typing and eliminates the `object[]` casts:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**Benefits:** compile-time type safety, no boxing/unboxing, and named tuple elements improve readability. This requires **MSTest 3.7+**.
